cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.SY

This paper discusses recursive stochastic algorithms for solving optimization and decision problems, which are commonly studied in the machine learning and control systems communities. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) due to the focus on optimization algorithms. The paper also discusses iterated random maps, which are related to dynamical systems and chaos theory, suggesting a possible fit with cs.DS (Dynamical Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
